.TH "batadv_tp_cwnd" 9 "batadv_tp_cwnd" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_tp_cwnd \- compute the new cwnd size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" batadv_tp_cwnd
.BI "(u32 base "  ","
.BI "u32 increment "  ","
.BI "u32 min "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "base" 12
base cwnd size value
.IP "increment" 12
the value to add to base to get the new size
.IP "min" 12
minimum cwnd value (usually MSS)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return the new cwnd size and ensure it does not exceed the Advertised
Receiver Window size. It is wrapped around safely.
For details refer to Section 3.1 of RFC5681
.SH "RETURN"
new congestion window size in bytes
